------------------------------------------------------------------------
r392 | dvhart | 2003-10-12 15:27:11 -0700 (Sun, 12 Oct 2003) | 2 lines

new composition model implemented, to add a widget to a container you should now call my_widget->parent(my_container) NOT my_container->add(my_widget).  The reason for this is that calling add() might give the impression a widget can be in more than container at a time, while calling parent() is clear that a widget only belongs in one.  Also some updates to scroll_box.  Still need to write the create() routines without parent pointers

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r391 | carter | 2003-10-12 08:24:37 -0700 (Sun, 12 Oct 2003) | 2 lines

Fixed the lines to origin bug (how did the surface ever work?)

